					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> I don't want anything clipped.</div>Only solution i can think of that prevents sprites from wrapping around because of being scrolled out that doesn't disable the leftmost column is to check if OAMbuffer+OAMstruct::xpos,x is &gt; #248 and if so move them off-screen on the y axis. It means sprites will snap in/out to the far right, but it can be considered cleaner. <br />For wider metasprites, you may also want to do some checks to the left with the conditionals based on the entities' xpos and xradius so that you can conditionally &quot;cancel&quot; tiles that have wrapped <em>all </em>the way around.<br /><br />It helps make a simpler algorithm if all entities are <em>either </em>center-aligned or left-aligned, xpos-wise. Don't mix anchorpoints.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
					
